<div id="review_1919548943" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1919548943" />
    <a title="Betül" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18248241-bet-l"><img alt="Betül" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1540845592p2/18248241.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1919548943?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Betül" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Betül" href="/user/show/18248241-bet-l">Betül</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1919548943" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17781009211477080648">&quot;I have lived, as they say, keeping myself to myself, that is, utterly alone-alone entirely alone. Do you know what it means to be alone?&quot;<br/><br/>I think Dostoyevsky knows the answer very well, again i thought and asked to myself what kind of an extraordinary life that this man lived inspiring him to create extraordinary characters like the one in this short story. <br/><br/>I wish i could learn the name of the hero of the story. With his pure heart, he lives in his dream world, what a character, he dreams even i</span>
  <span id="freeText17781009211477080648" style="display:none">"I have lived, as they say, keeping myself to myself, that is, utterly alone-alone entirely alone. Do you know what it means to be alone?"<br /><br />I think Dostoyevsky knows the answer very well, again i thought and asked to myself what kind of an extraordinary life that this man lived inspiring him to create extraordinary characters like the one in this short story. <br /><br />I wish i could learn the name of the hero of the story. With his pure heart, he lives in his dream world, what a character, he dreams even in his dreams until somebody to show up and his "white nights" start. I thought, maybe, we live our lives by dreaming in our daily realities, maybe life is a dream until we fall in love with someone. Happinesses, joys, sorrows, disappointments and cravings of love show us the real life.<br /><br />Like other Dostoyevsky novels i have read before, i saw reflections of my own psyche. I think, this explains why i am very much attracted to this one. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17781009211477080648" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


