<div id="review_1925489899" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1925489899" />
    <a title="Ram Alsrougi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/55615999-ram-alsrougi"><img alt="Ram Alsrougi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1563277979p2/55615999.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1925489899?book_show_action=true">Apr 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ram Alsrougi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ram Alsrougi" href="/user/show/55615999-ram-alsrougi">Ram Alsrougi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1925489899" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10053580109684145134">My life in a nutshell!<br/><br/>&quot;White Nights&quot; marks my second meeting with Dostoevsky and I am certainly not disappointed.<br/><br/>The style of this short novel is enchanting. History seems to be veiled by that fog which is proper to dreams.<br/><br/>In the middle of the fog only two characters move during the nights, their souls approach for a moment.<br/>I don&apos;t want to say more about this little gem.<br/>I only know that a single reading is not enough to grasp its beauty in its entirety.<br/><br/>For now I put it virtually on the bedside t</span>
  <span id="freeText10053580109684145134" style="display:none">My life in a nutshell!<br /><br />"White Nights" marks my second meeting with Dostoevsky and I am certainly not disappointed.<br /><br />The style of this short novel is enchanting. History seems to be veiled by that fog which is proper to dreams.<br /><br />In the middle of the fog only two characters move during the nights, their souls approach for a moment.<br />I don't want to say more about this little gem.<br />I only know that a single reading is not enough to grasp its beauty in its entirety.<br /><br />For now I put it virtually on the bedside table. Nights will come when I will feel the need to read it again!. ❤❤</span>
  <a data-text-id="10053580109684145134" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


